This involves building the different components of the application
Frontend
Backend 
The prediction model and 
Integrating third-party services like payment gateways and shipping providers


First part - Frontend using React.Js
Navigation Bar:

Define a React component for the navigation bar.
Use React Router to define the routes for different sections of the app.
Add links or buttons to the navigation bar that navigate to different routes.
Dashboard:

Define a React component for the dashboard.
Use a data visualization library such as Chart.js or D3.js to display real-time stock market data.
Use APIs or back-end systems to retrieve the data and update the dashboard.
Prediction Form:

Define a React component for the prediction form.
Use a form library such as Formik or React Hook Form to create the form and handle user input.
Use APIs or back-end systems to process the user input and generate predictions.
Display the predictions using a data visualization library or table component.
News Feed:

Define a React component for the news feed.
Use APIs or back-end systems to retrieve the latest news and events related to the stock market and specific companies.
Display the news using a news feed component or list view.
User Account:

Define a React component for the user account section.
Use APIs or back-end systems to retrieve and display user account information, such as their portfolio, transaction history, and account balance.
Allow users to manage their account settings, such as notification preferences and account security.
Authentication and Authorization:

Define a React component for the login form.
Use authentication and authorization libraries such as Firebase Authentication or Auth0 to handle user authentication and authorization.
Store user authentication state in a React context or Redux store.
Mobile Responsiveness:

Use responsive design techniques such as CSS media queries to adjust the layout of the application based on the device screen size.
Use responsive components or layouts to ensure that the application is mobile-friendly.
